1
00:01:15,700 --> 00:01:20,940
=About Love=

2
00:01:21,000 --> 00:01:23,940
=Episode 2=

3
00:01:25,460 --> 00:01:26,300
I'm here.

4
00:01:27,900 --> 00:01:28,740
Ah.

5
00:01:29,930 --> 00:01:30,770
Well,

6
00:01:32,740 --> 00:01:33,580
get some rest early.

7
00:01:34,490 --> 00:01:35,330
Yeah.

8
00:01:35,690 --> 00:01:36,540
You too.

9
00:01:39,850 --> 00:01:40,690
How about

10
00:01:40,820 --> 00:01:42,690
we go grab a coffee?

11
00:01:45,540 --> 00:01:46,620
Are you serious?

12
00:01:48,460 --> 00:01:49,570
Not really. Maybe tomorrow?

13
00:01:49,740 --> 00:01:50,660
It's a bit late today.

14
00:01:51,180 --> 00:01:52,260
Let's get coffee tomorrow.

15
00:01:53,380 --> 00:01:54,220
Okay.

16
00:01:55,020 --> 00:01:55,900
Oh, right, I just...

17
00:01:56,190 --> 00:01:57,050
When I passed by your place,

18
00:01:57,050 --> 00:01:58,210
there was a cafe nearby.

19
00:01:58,620 --> 00:01:59,460
How's that place?

20
00:01:59,740 --> 00:02:00,620
Pretty nice actually.

21
00:02:01,180 --> 00:02:03,100
But they don't have
many types of coffee beans.

22
00:02:03,290 --> 00:02:05,290
The place we went to today
had a bit more options.

23
00:02:06,490 --> 00:02:07,410
Alright.

24
00:02:07,410 --> 00:02:09,060
Then let's go to the same place
again tomorrow.

25
00:02:10,940 --> 00:02:11,820
Sure.

26
00:02:12,690 --> 00:02:14,340
I'll come pick you up tomorrow.

27
00:02:16,220 --> 00:02:17,060
Yeah.

28
00:02:21,010 --> 00:02:21,940
I'm heading out then.

29
00:02:22,540 --> 00:02:23,380
Oh, okay.

30
00:02:24,170 --> 00:02:25,130
- Bye.
- Bye.

31
00:02:26,940 --> 00:02:27,780
Hey, wait a second!

32
00:02:29,730 --> 00:02:30,570
Your shoes.

33
00:02:34,130 --> 00:02:35,100
Thanks for this.

34
00:02:35,500 --> 00:02:36,340
You're welcome.

35
00:02:36,730 --> 00:02:37,570
I'm off.

36
00:02:37,820 --> 00:02:38,660
- Good night.
- Bye.

37
00:02:38,660 --> 00:02:39,500
Bye.

38
00:03:07,890 --> 00:03:09,450
(I once navigated)

39
00:03:09,450 --> 00:03:11,500
(among those men with masterful acting.)

40
00:03:12,410 --> 00:03:15,940
(There are improv performances
full of technique but devoid of emotion.)

41
00:03:17,260 --> 00:03:19,820
(Never affecting
the villains' genuine performances.)

42
00:03:21,170 --> 00:03:23,940
(I know this isn't a fair game.)

43
00:03:25,570 --> 00:03:26,570
(But who's to blame)

44
00:03:27,170 --> 00:03:28,220
(for leading them)

45
00:03:28,220 --> 00:03:30,570
(to this forbidden land
of eternal damnation?)

46
00:03:33,500 --> 00:03:35,660
(I've seen enough
of worldly love stories.)

47
00:03:36,060 --> 00:03:37,890
(They all feel dull and predictable.)

48
00:03:39,100 --> 00:03:41,540
(But when that special person appears,)

49
00:03:42,340 --> 00:03:45,260
(I feel like
an inexperienced extra actor)

50
00:03:45,540 --> 00:03:48,410
(before him.)

51
00:03:55,570 --> 00:03:56,410
What's wrong?

52
00:04:20,900 --> 00:04:21,740
Morning.

53
00:04:21,930 --> 00:04:22,770
Morning!

54
00:04:25,100 --> 00:04:26,020
Got you breakfast.

55
00:04:28,610 --> 00:04:30,810
How'd you know
I love this shop's pan-fried buns?

56
00:04:31,980 --> 00:04:33,050
You posted it on Moments.

57
00:04:33,050 --> 00:04:33,930
Come on, get in the car.

58
00:04:35,170 --> 00:04:36,140
Thanks.

59
00:04:41,490 --> 00:04:43,220
(With his seemingly icy,)

60
00:04:43,220 --> 00:04:44,580
(indifferent thoughtfulness,)

61
00:04:44,980 --> 00:04:45,930
(he recklessly)

62
00:04:45,930 --> 00:04:48,930
(awakened the innocent heart
I once kept hidden.)

63
00:04:56,850 --> 00:04:57,690
Here.

64
00:04:58,610 --> 00:04:59,610
No scallions or cilantro.

65
00:04:59,620 --> 00:05:00,780
- Thanks.
- Here.

66
00:05:02,980 --> 00:05:03,850
Wait a second.

67
00:05:05,100 --> 00:05:06,580
I learned

68
00:05:07,250 --> 00:05:08,340
a "noodle-eating hack" online.

69
00:05:09,810 --> 00:05:10,660
Now it won't burn your mouth.

70
00:05:10,780 --> 00:05:12,410
(He's so ordinary,)

71
00:05:12,610 --> 00:05:14,290
(yet somehow truly remarkable.)

72
00:05:15,250 --> 00:05:16,810
(I've never heard a fake compliment)

73
00:05:16,810 --> 00:05:19,050
(from him.)

74
00:05:19,730 --> 00:05:21,280
(But his care for me)

75
00:05:21,290 --> 00:05:22,140
Eat up.

76
00:05:22,140 --> 00:05:23,810
(is in every little detail.)

77
00:05:25,700 --> 00:05:27,460
Text me when you get home.

78
00:05:28,460 --> 00:05:29,900
- Okay?
- Alright.

79
00:05:30,900 --> 00:05:31,780
You should head back.

80
00:05:32,050 --> 00:05:33,150
- I'll get going then.
- Yeah.

81
00:05:34,220 --> 00:05:35,490
- Bye.
- Bye.

82
00:05:37,540 --> 00:05:40,020
(Love feels like such a heavy word.)

83
00:05:40,370 --> 00:05:41,340
(I don't really believe in it.)

84
00:05:41,700 --> 00:05:42,850
(And I'm not eager to talk about it.)

85
00:05:47,660 --> 00:05:48,660
(But aside from love,)

86
00:05:49,220 --> 00:05:50,780
(I can't figure out)

87
00:05:50,980 --> 00:05:52,290
(what else connects us.)

88
00:05:53,250 --> 00:05:54,370
(I'm growing more certain)

89
00:05:54,850 --> 00:05:56,140
(that life shines brighter)

90
00:05:56,140 --> 00:05:58,290
(because of a man)

91
00:05:58,290 --> 00:05:59,730
(who belongs only to me.)

92
00:06:03,340 --> 00:06:05,290
(I've started acting
like a student again,)

93
00:06:05,530 --> 00:06:06,410
(checking zodiac signs)

94
00:06:06,410 --> 00:06:07,410
(and reading the love guides.)

95
00:06:08,250 --> 00:06:09,540
(I can spend two hours)

96
00:06:09,900 --> 00:06:11,580
(getting perfectly dressed for someone.)

97
00:06:17,100 --> 00:06:19,810
(I get restless over a late call)

98
00:06:19,810 --> 00:06:21,170
(or message.)

99
00:06:21,260 --> 00:06:23,660
(Bei)

100
00:06:28,100 --> 00:06:29,660
(Moments)
(But I still can't help feeling scared.)

101
00:06:29,810 --> 00:06:31,220
(Mingmig lets me get close to the lens.)
(Could this dazzling happiness)

102
00:06:31,540 --> 00:06:34,700
(be just a dream or an illusion of joy?)

103
00:06:36,780 --> 00:06:37,850
Who is she?

104
00:06:40,050 --> 00:06:41,020
That little girl.

105
00:06:41,410 --> 00:06:42,610
I haven't seen her before.

106
00:06:43,060 --> 00:06:43,900
Her name's Mingming.

107
00:06:43,900 --> 00:06:45,220
She's new at our shop.

108
00:06:46,170 --> 00:06:47,010
Oh.

109
00:06:49,170 --> 00:06:50,780
You really want to know the result.

110
00:06:51,540 --> 00:06:53,220
Aren't you worried it might upset you?

111
00:06:56,370 --> 00:06:57,290
Would it?

112
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:24,340
(Suddenly,)

113
00:07:25,730 --> 00:07:28,050
(I understand those flustered women.)

114
00:07:29,930 --> 00:07:31,460
(The more beautiful the love,)

115
00:07:32,810 --> 00:07:34,490
(the greater the fear of losing it.)

116
00:07:35,850 --> 00:07:38,020
(Who can be completely certain?)

117
00:08:00,900 --> 00:08:01,740
Welcome!

118
00:08:02,780 --> 00:08:03,620
Sen?

119
00:08:04,340 --> 00:08:05,460
Bei hasn't arrived yet.

120
00:08:05,900 --> 00:08:06,850
I'm not here for him.

121
00:08:07,460 --> 00:08:08,540
I came for you.

122
00:08:09,220 --> 00:08:10,060
Oh.

123
00:08:12,410 --> 00:08:14,220
So, how's it going?
Having a good time here?

124
00:08:14,410 --> 00:08:15,250
Yeah.

125
00:08:15,250 --> 00:08:16,370
Bei's been looking out for me.

126
00:08:23,220 --> 00:08:24,220
Try this cake.

127
00:08:24,540 --> 00:08:25,490
The shop just opened.

128
00:08:25,610 --> 00:08:26,610
Everyone says it tastes great.

129
00:08:27,050 --> 00:08:28,850
I'm still working. I'll eat later.

130
00:08:29,460 --> 00:08:30,370
Thanks.

131
00:08:31,850 --> 00:08:33,820
Then I'll pick you up after work.

132
00:08:33,820 --> 00:08:34,700
No need.

133
00:08:34,700 --> 00:08:35,820
I've got something to do tonight.

134
00:08:38,650 --> 00:08:39,490
You...

135
00:08:39,820 --> 00:08:40,940
You're not going to see him, are you?

136
00:08:40,940 --> 00:08:41,850
No.

137
00:08:44,010 --> 00:08:44,940
You're starting again.

138
00:08:46,370 --> 00:08:47,460
Right. Sorry.

139
00:08:47,820 --> 00:08:48,980
I'm just worried about you.

140
00:08:51,940 --> 00:08:52,850
Welcome!

141
00:08:53,490 --> 00:08:54,580
I need to attend to customers.
Talk later.

142
00:08:54,730 --> 00:08:56,730
I'm free anytime.
I'll wait for your message.

143
00:08:58,770 --> 00:08:59,610
Hello.

144
00:09:00,220 --> 00:09:01,500
(Mingming)

145
00:09:02,460 --> 00:09:03,300
Mingming?

146
00:09:03,610 --> 00:09:04,450
Yes.

147
00:09:11,610 --> 00:09:13,300
How may I help you?

148
00:09:14,420 --> 00:09:16,100
What kind of services do you offer here?

149
00:09:16,820 --> 00:09:18,060
Let me give you a quick introduction.

150
00:09:18,220 --> 00:09:19,060
This way, please.

151
00:09:19,850 --> 00:09:22,370
Our main business is
luxury goods authentication.

152
00:09:22,370 --> 00:09:23,700
Our boss studied

153
00:09:23,700 --> 00:09:25,300
professional luxury management

154
00:09:25,490 --> 00:09:26,640
and authentication techniques in the UK.

155
00:09:27,060 --> 00:09:28,580
Of course, we also provide

156
00:09:28,580 --> 00:09:29,850
maintenance
and repair services for bags,

157
00:09:29,850 --> 00:09:30,690
as well as

158
00:09:30,940 --> 00:09:32,180
recycling and consignment services.

159
00:09:34,530 --> 00:09:36,460
By the way, the edge paint
on my bag came apart.

160
00:09:37,010 --> 00:09:37,980
Can you fix it?

161
00:09:38,100 --> 00:09:38,980
Let me take a look for you.

162
00:09:39,530 --> 00:09:40,370
Sorry.

163
00:09:40,700 --> 00:09:42,010
There's also a small bag inside.

164
00:09:44,100 --> 00:09:46,300
Ah, your edge paint issue
isn't too severe.

165
00:09:46,850 --> 00:09:47,850
If you're not in a hurry,

166
00:09:47,980 --> 00:09:49,180
you can wait over there for a bit.

167
00:09:49,490 --> 00:09:50,330
Ah, no rush.

168
00:10:01,100 --> 00:10:02,010
Xiaoxi!

169
00:10:03,650 --> 00:10:04,530
Why so early?

170
00:10:04,820 --> 00:10:06,580
I came early, so I just came in first.

171
00:10:07,580 --> 00:10:09,420
How is it? What about the shop?

172
00:10:11,300 --> 00:10:12,140
Yeah.

173
00:10:12,370 --> 00:10:13,940
Enthusiastic, attentive service.

174
00:10:13,940 --> 00:10:14,780
Very professional.

175
00:10:15,010 --> 00:10:16,940
Most importantly,
the boss's lady is satisfied.

176
00:10:18,100 --> 00:10:19,100
Nonsense.

177
00:10:20,820 --> 00:10:21,770
Mingming, come.

178
00:10:22,010 --> 00:10:22,850
Let me introduce you.

179
00:10:24,460 --> 00:10:26,010
This is my girlfriend,

180
00:10:26,250 --> 00:10:27,090
Li Xiaoxi.

181
00:10:27,490 --> 00:10:29,060
This is Mingming,
the one I told you about.

182
00:10:29,250 --> 00:10:30,180
Hi, sister-in-law.

183
00:10:30,180 --> 00:10:31,220
You should've said so earlier.

184
00:10:31,580 --> 00:10:32,420
Hello.

185
00:10:34,220 --> 00:10:36,850
Was that your boyfriend earlier?

186
00:10:39,100 --> 00:10:41,180
This cake is from a trendy
internet-famous shop. It's hard to get.

187
00:10:42,980 --> 00:10:43,820
Oh, really?

188
00:10:44,060 --> 00:10:45,100
He treats you really well.

189
00:10:45,940 --> 00:10:46,940
Sen just stopped by?

190
00:10:47,490 --> 00:10:48,330
He just left.

191
00:10:48,850 --> 00:10:49,690
You know him?

192
00:10:50,460 --> 00:10:51,730
Of course, he's my buddy.

193
00:10:54,490 --> 00:10:55,610
Ah, that explains it.

194
00:10:56,420 --> 00:10:58,060
If you like this cake,

195
00:10:58,610 --> 00:11:00,300
I'll take you to get some later, deal?

196
00:11:01,100 --> 00:11:03,100
So this is how Bei is when he's in love?

197
00:11:03,730 --> 00:11:04,700
Long live the boss!

198
00:11:07,370 --> 00:11:09,340
Stop it. Who said I'm the boss's lady?

199
00:11:10,850 --> 00:11:12,650
Who's this amazing person?

200
00:11:12,850 --> 00:11:14,220
Got you hooked so fast?

201
00:11:16,010 --> 00:11:17,060
Why not bring him out to meet me?

202
00:11:19,460 --> 00:11:20,490
What's the rush?

203
00:11:21,700 --> 00:11:23,460
Meeting the besties is a big deal.

204
00:11:24,250 --> 00:11:25,340
It's still a bit early.

205
00:11:25,650 --> 00:11:27,130
Afraid he won't pass my test?

206
00:11:27,580 --> 00:11:28,530
He's different.

207
00:11:29,060 --> 00:11:30,580
Oh?

208
00:11:31,580 --> 00:11:33,340
Who was it that told me

209
00:11:33,650 --> 00:11:35,730
that every girl says
her boyfriend is different

210
00:11:35,730 --> 00:11:37,300
at the start of a relationship?

211
00:11:38,010 --> 00:11:39,370
And it's because of

212
00:11:39,370 --> 00:11:41,250
hormones and endorphins?

213
00:11:44,130 --> 00:11:46,700
I used to think my husband was unique

214
00:11:47,180 --> 00:11:49,300
and different from 99% of men.

215
00:11:50,130 --> 00:11:51,060
And the result?

216
00:11:52,370 --> 00:11:53,580
Now he's my ex-husband.

217
00:11:56,300 --> 00:11:57,220
You got divorced?

218
00:11:58,850 --> 00:12:00,180
He was cheating.

219
00:12:02,300 --> 00:12:03,250
When did this happen?

220
00:12:04,250 --> 00:12:05,370
Apparently, that cheating pair

221
00:12:05,370 --> 00:12:06,770
has been together for a while.

222
00:12:07,940 --> 00:12:09,340
Every time he told me
he was on a business trip,

223
00:12:09,340 --> 00:12:10,770
I stupidly believed him

224
00:12:11,700 --> 00:12:13,370
until I saw the two of them
enter a hotel.

225
00:12:15,770 --> 00:12:17,580
Thanks to that vixen,

226
00:12:19,250 --> 00:12:20,980
my life also got its own cheesy

227
00:12:20,980 --> 00:12:22,820
"caught-in-the-act" plot.

228
00:12:24,370 --> 00:12:26,250
Honey, you've worked hard.

229
00:12:26,650 --> 00:12:28,580
You should've seen him

230
00:12:28,980 --> 00:12:30,890
frantically pulling up his pants,

231
00:12:30,890 --> 00:12:32,490
as if I'd never seen it before.

232
00:12:35,130 --> 00:12:36,300
It was honestly hilarious.

233
00:12:37,010 --> 00:12:38,610
So tell me, who makes you happier?

234
00:12:38,820 --> 00:12:40,580
I was wrong. It's me who hurt you.

235
00:12:41,010 --> 00:12:41,940
Her, or me?

236
00:12:42,890 --> 00:12:44,340
Yingtao, don't be like this.

237
00:12:44,340 --> 00:12:45,180
Honey,

238
00:12:45,730 --> 00:12:50,530
does she please you more than I do?

239
00:12:50,530 --> 00:12:51,370
That's enough!

240
00:13:01,220 --> 00:13:03,220
Right then, I swore to make them pay.

241
00:13:03,650 --> 00:13:04,940
But later, I thought about it again.

242
00:13:05,220 --> 00:13:06,420
Why should I?

243
00:13:06,850 --> 00:13:07,980
Why should I debase myself

244
00:13:07,980 --> 00:13:09,100
over a man?

245
00:13:09,700 --> 00:13:11,340
But I really can't forgive him.

246
00:13:12,300 --> 00:13:14,850
The thought of that scene makes me sick.

247
00:13:15,370 --> 00:13:16,820
So I just got divorced.

248
00:13:18,180 --> 00:13:19,580
There's no going back anyway.

249
00:13:21,100 --> 00:13:21,940
(I'm sorry.)

250
00:13:22,730 --> 00:13:24,250
(I should've told you back then.)

251
00:13:25,100 --> 00:13:26,130
(It's my fault.)

252
00:13:26,420 --> 00:13:27,260
I need to use the restroom.

253
00:13:31,890 --> 00:13:34,130
It's a shame Yingtao

254
00:13:34,300 --> 00:13:35,340
didn't introduce us sooner.

255
00:13:38,130 --> 00:13:39,490
That scum.

256
00:13:40,460 --> 00:13:41,850
Why didn't you tell me then

257
00:13:41,850 --> 00:13:43,890
to test him before marrying him?

258
00:13:44,300 --> 00:13:45,940
If that had happened,

259
00:13:45,940 --> 00:13:47,460
you probably wouldn't
have gotten married

260
00:13:49,300 --> 00:13:50,580
and wouldn't be getting divorced now.

261
00:13:51,340 --> 00:13:52,180
Right?

262
00:13:55,060 --> 00:13:55,900
It's all in the past.

263
00:13:57,580 --> 00:13:59,580
Enough about me.
Tell me about your boyfriend.

264
00:14:00,730 --> 00:14:02,700
You've experienced
so much betrayal yourself.

265
00:14:03,420 --> 00:14:05,130
Aren't you afraid he'll...?

266
00:14:05,130 --> 00:14:06,580
I don't think he's that kind of person.

267
00:14:06,730 --> 00:14:08,180
You haven't even tested him.

268
00:14:08,180 --> 00:14:09,460
How do you know he's not?

269
00:14:10,490 --> 00:14:11,460
Is that necessary?

270
00:14:12,460 --> 00:14:13,820
Yes, absolutely.

271
00:14:14,010 --> 00:14:15,460
If you truly love him,

272
00:14:15,460 --> 00:14:16,700
you have to confirm he is yours,

273
00:14:17,130 --> 00:14:18,770
exclusively yours.

274
00:14:19,850 --> 00:14:21,530
I don't want you to repeat my mistakes.

275
00:14:25,060 --> 00:14:26,180
Then...

276
00:14:26,610 --> 00:14:27,450
No need to worry.

277
00:14:27,770 --> 00:14:28,700
Leave it to me.

278
00:14:28,700 --> 00:14:29,540
I'll take care of it.

279
00:14:31,530 --> 00:14:32,820
Let's treat it

280
00:14:33,530 --> 00:14:34,370
like a reality show.

281
00:14:34,610 --> 00:14:35,820
(I never thought the day would come)

282
00:14:36,300 --> 00:14:38,130
(when I'd be plotting my own)

283
00:14:38,250 --> 00:14:39,340
(romantic suspense film.)

284
00:14:40,340 --> 00:14:41,650
(But unlike before,)

285
00:14:42,220 --> 00:14:43,650
(this time, I'm neither the director)

286
00:14:44,060 --> 00:14:45,060
(nor the actor.)

287
00:14:45,850 --> 00:14:47,010
(I'm just part of the audience.)

288
00:14:47,890 --> 00:14:50,220
(I feel an unprecedented anxiety.)

289
00:14:51,100 --> 00:14:51,940
(This time,)

290
00:14:52,300 --> 00:14:54,250
(the ending remains just a mystery.)

291
00:14:54,980 --> 00:14:55,890
(But this time,)

292
00:14:56,220 --> 00:14:57,340
(I desperately hope)

293
00:14:57,530 --> 00:14:59,890
(that one-in-a-million chance
might happen.)

294
00:15:01,300 --> 00:15:02,140
Excuse me, handsome?

295
00:15:02,580 --> 00:15:03,770
Sorry to disturb you.

296
00:15:04,010 --> 00:15:05,100
Could you tell me

297
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:07,100
how to get to Huaxi Park?

298
00:15:08,100 --> 00:15:09,460
Go to the end of
that intersection up ahead,

299
00:15:09,460 --> 00:15:10,650
then turn left.

300
00:15:10,850 --> 00:15:12,460
After that, go through
three traffic lights

301
00:15:13,100 --> 00:15:14,460
and probably further...

302
00:15:14,460 --> 00:15:16,460
That sounds too complicated.

303
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:17,940
How about this?

304
00:15:17,940 --> 00:15:19,850
Could you show me the way, handsome?

305
00:15:20,770 --> 00:15:21,610
Huh?

306
00:15:21,730 --> 00:15:22,610
Oh, I'm so sorry.

307
00:15:22,610 --> 00:15:24,250
It's kind of rude for me
to ask like this.

308
00:15:24,700 --> 00:15:27,180
It's just that my bag

309
00:15:27,180 --> 00:15:29,130
and my phone got stolen today.

310
00:15:29,250 --> 00:15:31,820
I genuinely don't know
how to get to Huaxi Park.

311
00:15:32,890 --> 00:15:33,730
So...

312
00:15:34,060 --> 00:15:35,300
Alright then,

313
00:15:35,650 --> 00:15:36,580
I'll take you there.

314
00:15:36,580 --> 00:15:37,460
Okay!

315
00:15:37,460 --> 00:15:38,300
Here, take this.

316
00:15:38,300 --> 00:15:39,230
Thanks, handsome.

317
00:15:41,010 --> 00:15:42,850
I'm so lucky to have run into you today.

318
00:15:43,100 --> 00:15:45,300
Otherwise, I'd have no idea what to do.

319
00:15:46,850 --> 00:15:47,940
Yeah.

320
00:15:47,940 --> 00:15:48,980
Come on, get in the car.

321
00:15:49,770 --> 00:15:51,180
He's got a spare umbrella.

322
00:15:54,820 --> 00:15:55,890
Come on, get in.

323
00:15:56,100 --> 00:15:57,060
Thanks.

324
00:16:00,460 --> 00:16:01,700
Do you know...?

325
00:16:02,370 --> 00:16:03,210
Sir!

326
00:16:06,130 --> 00:16:07,340
It's fine. I'll cover the fare.

327
00:16:07,730 --> 00:16:09,370
Sir, how much to Huaxi Park?

328
00:16:09,370 --> 00:16:10,210
Ten yuan.

329
00:16:10,340 --> 00:16:11,700
Okay, sent it.

330
00:16:12,010 --> 00:16:14,060
No, it's not about the money.

331
00:16:14,060 --> 00:16:14,900
It's about...

332
00:16:15,180 --> 00:16:16,130
Anything else?

333
00:16:18,060 --> 00:16:19,100
Your umbrella.

334
00:16:19,820 --> 00:16:20,730
Keep it, I don't need it anymore.

335
00:16:21,250 --> 00:16:22,370
Wait, you...

336
00:16:30,100 --> 00:16:31,700
Don't get too proud yet.

337
00:16:31,820 --> 00:16:33,100
His "fortune" is just beginning.

338
00:16:34,100 --> 00:16:35,610
Hold on!

339
00:16:38,010 --> 00:16:38,890
Thanks.

340
00:17:17,220 --> 00:17:18,060
Hello.

341
00:17:19,940 --> 00:17:20,780
Hi.

342
00:17:22,770 --> 00:17:23,610
What's wrong?

343
00:17:24,050 --> 00:17:25,330
Don't you recognize me anymore?

344
00:17:26,730 --> 00:17:27,980
Who are you?

345
00:17:28,530 --> 00:17:30,660
We see each other
in the elevator every day.

346
00:17:32,010 --> 00:17:33,460
Sorry, I never really noticed.

347
00:17:34,660 --> 00:17:35,940
On the street,

348
00:17:36,250 --> 00:17:37,570
I turn quite a lot of heads.

349
00:17:38,050 --> 00:17:39,730
People say I look like

350
00:17:39,980 --> 00:17:42,380
that internet celebrity,
Mengmeng. Do you think so?

351
00:17:44,140 --> 00:17:45,220
Really sorry.

352
00:17:45,220 --> 00:17:46,660
Many girls get work done now...

353
00:17:47,660 --> 00:17:50,250
They all look pretty similar, so...

354
00:17:50,460 --> 00:17:51,300
I don't really remember.

355
00:17:51,660 --> 00:17:53,730
Did he just say I've had work done?

356
00:17:54,140 --> 00:17:55,180
Do I even look like I did?

357
00:17:56,090 --> 00:17:57,490
No. He's just...

358
00:17:57,620 --> 00:17:58,980
never been good with words.

359
00:17:58,980 --> 00:18:00,050
Don't take it to heart.

360
00:18:00,050 --> 00:18:02,140
I mean, I'm still adored
everywhere I go,

361
00:18:02,140 --> 00:18:03,730
and flowers would bloom for me, right?

362
00:18:03,730 --> 00:18:04,600
Yeah.

363
00:18:04,610 --> 00:18:06,660
He actually said
I look like I got work done?

364
00:18:06,660 --> 00:18:07,730
I'm so mad right now.

365
00:18:13,940 --> 00:18:14,780
Hey!

366
00:18:19,900 --> 00:18:20,810
Calling me?

367
00:18:20,810 --> 00:18:22,940
I just broke up.
He doesn't want me anymore.

368
00:18:23,730 --> 00:18:24,770
It really hurts.

369
00:18:24,980 --> 00:18:26,380
Can you talk with me for a bit?

370
00:18:26,770 --> 00:18:27,610
Sure.

371
00:18:28,370 --> 00:18:29,220
Okay then.

372
00:18:29,220 --> 00:18:30,290
Wait for me a second, alright?

373
00:18:33,420 --> 00:18:34,260
Gong,

374
00:18:35,050 --> 00:18:36,860
there's a girl here who just broke up.

375
00:18:36,860 --> 00:18:38,010
Can you come over?

376
00:18:38,660 --> 00:18:40,570
Is she pretty? How's her figure?

377
00:18:40,570 --> 00:18:41,700
Is she my type?

378
00:18:43,460 --> 00:18:45,050
She's actually quite pretty.

379
00:18:45,050 --> 00:18:46,140
What kind of type do you like?

380
00:18:46,770 --> 00:18:48,900
Honestly, I'm fine with any kind.

381
00:18:49,290 --> 00:18:50,250
Send me the location.

382
00:18:50,250 --> 00:18:51,530
Keep an eye on her for me.
I'm on my way.

383
00:18:51,980 --> 00:18:52,860
Tone it down.

384
00:18:52,860 --> 00:18:53,940
I'll send you the address.

385
00:18:54,940 --> 00:18:55,780
I...

386
00:18:56,730 --> 00:18:57,860
I don't feel that bad anymore.

387
00:18:57,860 --> 00:18:59,700
I'm much better now. Thank you.

388
00:18:59,900 --> 00:19:01,010
No, my friend's almost here.

389
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:01,850
He's coming to comfort you.

390
00:19:02,570 --> 00:19:03,770
No need, goodbye.

391
00:19:04,980 --> 00:19:06,420
He's great at comforting people.

392
00:19:07,010 --> 00:19:07,900
Don't leave!

393
00:19:15,050 --> 00:19:17,770
He lets a few chances slip away.

394
00:19:20,010 --> 00:19:21,380
He must be really into you.

395
00:19:22,050 --> 00:19:23,420
But don't you think
that's kind of strange?

396
00:19:24,570 --> 00:19:26,620
How could a man
be so resistant to temptation?

397
00:19:28,860 --> 00:19:29,730
My dear,

398
00:19:29,730 --> 00:19:31,380
aren't you being a bit
flexing your happiness?

399
00:19:32,220 --> 00:19:34,010
Don't push your luck.

400
00:19:34,380 --> 00:19:35,220
You're asking for a slap.

401
00:19:36,010 --> 00:19:37,460
But the man I want

402
00:19:37,460 --> 00:19:39,570
is one who stays devoted
to me wholeheartedly

403
00:19:39,900 --> 00:19:41,010
and completely unmoved

404
00:19:41,010 --> 00:19:42,250
by any temptations.

405
00:19:43,980 --> 00:19:45,220
If he's not that kind of man,

406
00:19:46,010 --> 00:19:47,050
I'd rather not have him.

407
00:19:48,050 --> 00:19:49,220
Currently,

408
00:19:49,620 --> 00:19:50,900
that's exactly how he acts.

409
00:19:54,420 --> 00:19:55,660
But don't you feel

410
00:19:57,460 --> 00:19:58,460
something's missing?

411
00:20:00,730 --> 00:20:01,660
I think I get it now.

412
00:20:03,420 --> 00:20:04,860
It's because it's always outside,

413
00:20:04,860 --> 00:20:05,940
and it's not convenient.

414
00:20:06,320 --> 00:20:08,760
We need to get inside
and use stronger tactics.

415
00:20:09,380 --> 00:20:10,220
Alright,

416
00:20:10,620 --> 00:20:11,530
we can give it one last shot.

417
00:20:13,010 --> 00:20:14,380
We need to find someone

418
00:20:14,570 --> 00:20:16,620
who has all the charm and allure,

419
00:20:16,770 --> 00:20:18,860
stunning and cinematic.

420
00:20:19,660 --> 00:20:20,500
A true goddess.

421
00:20:30,620 --> 00:20:31,460
Who are you looking for?

422
00:20:31,460 --> 00:20:33,700
Excuse me, does Mr. Bei live here?

423
00:20:33,990 --> 00:20:34,860
That's me.

424
00:20:34,860 --> 00:20:36,420
Hi, I'm

425
00:20:36,420 --> 00:20:37,810
from the Sisters Housekeeping Team.

426
00:20:38,330 --> 00:20:39,170
What do you mean?

427
00:20:39,420 --> 00:20:40,570
(Housekeeper Yingtao)
Our team has deep partnerships

428
00:20:40,570 --> 00:20:42,090
with major banks.

429
00:20:42,290 --> 00:20:44,900
As our esteemed Gold Card member,

430
00:20:44,900 --> 00:20:46,250
you'll get one "freebie" opportunity

431
00:20:46,460 --> 00:20:47,730
for our

432
00:20:47,730 --> 00:20:49,010
deep-cleaning service.

433
00:20:52,290 --> 00:20:53,620
Fine, come in.

434
00:20:53,860 --> 00:20:54,700
Okay.

435
00:21:04,980 --> 00:21:06,980
I'll be cleaning
your place for four hours.

436
00:21:07,180 --> 00:21:08,140
During that time,

437
00:21:08,140 --> 00:21:09,730
I'll fulfill any request

438
00:21:10,570 --> 00:21:11,810
from the client.

439
00:21:14,460 --> 00:21:15,330
If...

440
00:21:15,860 --> 00:21:17,090
you need additional services...

441
00:21:17,090 --> 00:21:17,930
Wait, you...

442
00:21:18,490 --> 00:21:21,050
Sir, I haven't finished speaking.

443
00:21:21,380 --> 00:21:22,980
You really love to cut people off, huh?

444
00:21:24,620 --> 00:21:25,530
Wait, you...

445
00:21:25,940 --> 00:21:27,810
Do all housekeepers dress like this?

446
00:21:30,940 --> 00:21:32,330
Just call me Yingtao,

447
00:21:32,770 --> 00:21:34,330
like "cherry lips".

448
00:21:40,050 --> 00:21:40,890
Ah.

449
00:21:47,240 --> 00:21:49,230
♪Now we strike, defying gravity♪

450
00:21:49,240 --> 00:21:51,110
♪Now we strike,
breaking galactic distance♪

451
00:21:51,120 --> 00:21:53,020
♪Now we strike,
moving with the beat so free♪

452
00:21:53,020 --> 00:21:54,790
♪Now we strike,
reaching the highest peak♪

453
00:21:55,000 --> 00:21:56,830
♪Hold up, this is a brand-new reality♪

454
00:21:56,920 --> 00:21:58,870
♪Hold up, no more fantasies♪

455
00:21:58,880 --> 00:22:00,780
♪Hold up, no more aches♪

456
00:22:00,780 --> 00:22:02,790
♪Hold up, watch me take the lead♪

457
00:22:03,140 --> 00:22:06,740
♪Step out of the car,
no going off track♪

458
00:22:06,760 --> 00:22:08,510
♪I said we're on the move♪

459
00:22:08,520 --> 00:22:10,550
♪No taking the long way round♪

460
00:22:11,160 --> 00:22:12,350
♪Not the second place♪

461
00:22:12,360 --> 00:22:14,590
♪We win, taking all the trophies♪

462
00:22:15,080 --> 00:22:16,390
♪It all depends on you♪

463
00:22:16,400 --> 00:22:17,890
♪One day, we'll wake up♪

464
00:22:17,900 --> 00:22:19,140
No, Miss Yingtao.

465
00:22:21,900 --> 00:22:23,460
You've been

466
00:22:23,460 --> 00:22:25,570
tidying this spot
for nearly half an hour. Maybe...

467
00:22:26,380 --> 00:22:27,220
do something else?

468
00:22:27,900 --> 00:22:28,740
Alright, boss.

469
00:22:28,860 --> 00:22:30,330
Do you have any other instructions?

470
00:22:30,490 --> 00:22:31,330
Actually, I do.

471
00:22:32,530 --> 00:22:33,730
But this request of mine

472
00:22:33,730 --> 00:22:35,380
might exceed your usual duties.

473
00:22:37,250 --> 00:22:38,140
No problem.

474
00:22:38,140 --> 00:22:39,980
If I can do it, it's no problem.

475
00:22:40,220 --> 00:22:41,180
No problem?

476
00:22:41,840 --> 00:22:43,440
♪We won't stop, we'll give it our all♪

477
00:22:43,490 --> 00:22:44,460
That's great.

478
00:22:56,010 --> 00:22:56,860
Xiaoxi.

479
00:22:58,730 --> 00:22:59,570
What's wrong?

480
00:23:00,730 --> 00:23:02,140
I've been thinking for a long time.

481
00:23:02,570 --> 00:23:04,010
I still had to come and tell you.

482
00:23:08,090 --> 00:23:09,140
What happened?

483
00:23:10,660 --> 00:23:11,620
I'm sorry.

484
00:23:13,860 --> 00:23:14,730
Come on, get inside.

485
00:23:15,530 --> 00:23:16,370
Go inside.

486
00:23:21,140 --> 00:23:22,010
What's wrong?

487
00:23:24,530 --> 00:23:25,570
I think...

488
00:23:26,220 --> 00:23:28,460
testing him was a mistake.

489
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:31,140
I've fallen for him.

490
00:23:38,860 --> 00:23:39,700
Really?

491
00:23:40,980 --> 00:23:41,820
Yeah.

492
00:23:46,770 --> 00:23:48,220
Oh, how do I put this?

493
00:23:50,530 --> 00:23:51,980
Can you be a little more sincere?

494
00:23:53,700 --> 00:23:55,770
Put a bit more honesty into your act.

495
00:23:56,180 --> 00:23:57,020
Let's do another take.

496
00:23:57,220 --> 00:23:59,220
No, Xiaoxi, I mean it.

497
00:24:00,620 --> 00:24:03,010
I wish I'd never met him.

498
00:24:05,380 --> 00:24:06,620
Blame me, yell at me.

499
00:24:06,770 --> 00:24:08,050
You can even hit me,

500
00:24:08,530 --> 00:24:10,490
as long as it makes you feel better.

501
00:24:10,980 --> 00:24:12,490
But can I ask you for one thing?

502
00:24:13,860 --> 00:24:14,940
Give him to me.

503
00:24:21,700 --> 00:24:22,540
Better.

504
00:24:22,860 --> 00:24:23,900
Keep that state.

505
00:24:24,460 --> 00:24:25,300
But think about it.

506
00:24:25,310 --> 00:24:26,460
We've been friends for so many years.

507
00:24:27,570 --> 00:24:29,220
If you were in this situation,

508
00:24:29,220 --> 00:24:32,330
you'd probably feel
really guilty toward me.

509
00:24:32,900 --> 00:24:33,900
At least...

510
00:24:34,530 --> 00:24:36,660
shed a tiny bit of crocodile tears.

511
00:24:36,660 --> 00:24:38,180
That would feel real. Just one drop.

512
00:24:38,180 --> 00:24:39,290
Come on, let's try again.

513
00:24:40,490 --> 00:24:41,330
Think about it once more.

514
00:24:41,730 --> 00:24:42,570
Feel it deep inside.

515
00:24:43,420 --> 00:24:45,220
That kind of sadness from the heart.

516
00:24:45,940 --> 00:24:47,660
Xiaoxi!

517
00:24:48,770 --> 00:24:49,730
Did he hit you?

518
00:24:49,980 --> 00:24:50,860
I can't keep acting.

519
00:24:51,810 --> 00:24:52,860
I really can't keep acting.

520
00:24:53,460 --> 00:24:54,460
Not testing again?

521
00:24:55,380 --> 00:24:58,180
Why didn't you stop me
from going to his place?

522
00:24:58,850 --> 00:24:59,730
Do you know

523
00:24:59,730 --> 00:25:01,380
how I endured

524
00:25:01,380 --> 00:25:02,810
those hours

525
00:25:04,490 --> 00:25:06,250
at your boyfriend's house?

526
00:25:27,290 --> 00:25:28,500
So? Did it work?

527
00:25:29,090 --> 00:25:29,930
Yeah, it's all good now.

528
00:25:30,770 --> 00:25:32,010
Wow, you really nailed it.

529
00:25:32,570 --> 00:25:34,180
Any other requests?

530
00:25:36,330 --> 00:25:37,730
Actually, yeah. Come with me.

531
00:25:46,290 --> 00:25:47,770
You really worked hard today.

532
00:25:54,050 --> 00:25:54,890
All fixed?

533
00:25:56,730 --> 00:25:58,180
You're seriously amazing.

534
00:25:58,380 --> 00:25:59,570
There's nothing you can't do.

535
00:26:00,860 --> 00:26:01,700
After all, I'm a pro.

536
00:26:02,770 --> 00:26:04,810
I'll make sure you get
a five‑star review for this.

537
00:26:08,180 --> 00:26:09,460
I can't thank you enough.

538
00:26:10,050 --> 00:26:11,570
If there's more time,

539
00:26:11,900 --> 00:26:14,140
he even wants me
to clean his air conditioner.

540
00:26:14,530 --> 00:26:15,460
But the thing is,

541
00:26:15,980 --> 00:26:17,770
do you know
what he said to me in the end?

542
00:26:19,940 --> 00:26:20,780
Wait a second.

543
00:26:22,490 --> 00:26:23,330
Grab a bottle of water.

544
00:26:23,620 --> 00:26:24,460
Thanks.

545
00:26:24,810 --> 00:26:26,180
Wait, there's more.

546
00:26:32,050 --> 00:26:33,660
Can you help me take this downstairs?

547
00:26:35,490 --> 00:26:36,740
Yeah, sure.

548
00:26:36,940 --> 00:26:37,780
Thanks.

549
00:26:40,180 --> 00:26:41,700
You're really good at this stuff.

550
00:26:44,380 --> 00:26:46,570
Good at what? This is ridiculous.

551
00:26:46,730 --> 00:26:48,490
I've never been treated
like this in my life,

552
00:26:48,490 --> 00:26:49,380
so humiliated.

553
00:26:50,220 --> 00:26:51,060
That guy

554
00:26:51,220 --> 00:26:53,730
is the coldest person
I've ever tried to please.

555
00:26:54,290 --> 00:26:55,220
I'm so mad.

556
00:26:55,380 --> 00:26:56,460
It really hurts my pride.

557
00:26:56,980 --> 00:26:59,180
Calm down. Have an orange and cool off.

558
00:27:04,250 --> 00:27:07,090
Don't tell me you two
just didn't want to do chores,

559
00:27:07,220 --> 00:27:09,330
so you tricked me
into volunteering instead?

560
00:27:10,860 --> 00:27:12,050
No way, sis.

561
00:27:13,180 --> 00:27:15,570
This whole plan was your own idea.

562
00:27:17,010 --> 00:27:17,850
I don't care!

563
00:27:18,490 --> 00:27:19,530
Our little friendship just died.

564
00:27:19,730 --> 00:27:20,770
Alright, I know

565
00:27:21,220 --> 00:27:22,420
you suffered.

566
00:27:23,700 --> 00:27:24,660
I owe you one.

567
00:27:28,490 --> 00:27:30,570
Seriously, your boyfriend is sick.

568
00:27:30,570 --> 00:27:31,420
Serious issues.

569
00:27:31,420 --> 00:27:33,380
You'd better look into it.
Something's off with him.

570
00:27:33,660 --> 00:27:34,570
Totally off.

571
00:27:35,900 --> 00:27:36,770
I'll take it as it is.

572
00:27:37,770 --> 00:27:38,700
Don't you think

573
00:27:38,940 --> 00:27:40,940
the world becomes lovelier

574
00:27:41,220 --> 00:27:43,290
because of men like this?

575
00:27:45,730 --> 00:27:47,380
Didn't expect you
to enjoy movies like that.

576
00:27:49,220 --> 00:27:51,530
I love the starry galaxy at the end.

577
00:27:51,860 --> 00:27:52,810
It feels a bit like Socrates,

578
00:27:52,810 --> 00:27:54,180
gazing up at the stars.

579
00:27:55,620 --> 00:27:57,530
Alright. If there's a chance,
I'll go with you.

580
00:27:57,890 --> 00:27:58,730
Up to you.

581
00:27:58,730 --> 00:27:59,570
Okay.

582
00:28:00,570 --> 00:28:01,530
Two bottles of cola, please.

583
00:28:18,570 --> 00:28:19,410
Bei,

584
00:28:21,010 --> 00:28:22,220
isn't that Mingming over there?

585
00:28:23,050 --> 00:28:24,980
And the person next to her isn't Sen.

586
00:28:26,660 --> 00:28:28,380
Isn't Sen Mingming's boyfriend?

587
00:28:29,900 --> 00:28:31,290
Sen's been chasing her for ages.

588
00:28:31,730 --> 00:28:32,810
But Mingming still hasn't said yes.

589
00:28:34,530 --> 00:28:35,770
Sen's your good friend, right?

590
00:28:36,700 --> 00:28:37,540
Yeah.

591
00:28:37,770 --> 00:28:38,620
One is Sen.

592
00:28:38,860 --> 00:28:39,730
Then me, and Gong.

593
00:28:39,730 --> 00:28:41,090
The three of us grew up together.

594
00:28:41,660 --> 00:28:43,330
I've heard you mention Gong a lot.

595
00:28:43,330 --> 00:28:44,170
Who is he?

596
00:28:44,700 --> 00:28:45,570
Actually, tonight...

597
00:28:45,570 --> 00:28:46,940
I'm meeting up with Sen and Gong.

598
00:28:47,460 --> 00:28:48,330
How about

599
00:28:48,330 --> 00:28:49,570
you come along with us?

600
00:28:49,910 --> 00:28:50,770
I think

601
00:28:50,770 --> 00:28:52,050
it's time to introduce you.

602
00:28:52,940 --> 00:28:54,050
Why didn't you tell me earlier?

603
00:28:54,050 --> 00:28:55,460
I dressed so casually today.

604
00:28:55,460 --> 00:28:56,300
How embarrassing.

605
00:28:56,490 --> 00:28:58,180
You look great in anything.

606
00:28:58,530 --> 00:28:59,370
It's fine, don't worry.

607
00:29:00,490 --> 00:29:01,380
- Let's go.
- Yeah, let's go.

608
00:29:09,250 --> 00:29:10,860
That's the place. Shancheng Restaurant.

609
00:29:11,660 --> 00:29:12,500
Oh, it's here?

610
00:29:13,290 --> 00:29:14,700
Don't be fooled by how small it looks.

611
00:29:14,700 --> 00:29:17,490
The food tastes just as good
as any fancy hotel's.

612
00:29:17,900 --> 00:29:18,740
Plus,

613
00:29:19,090 --> 00:29:20,940
this place holds
the taste of my whole youth.

614
00:29:21,770 --> 00:29:22,900
That makes me even more curious.

615
00:29:23,150 --> 00:29:24,180
They should be upstairs.

616
00:29:24,790 --> 00:29:25,660
- Fatty!
- Bei, you're here!

617
00:29:25,660 --> 00:29:26,860
- Yeah.
- They're waiting upstairs.

618
00:29:26,860 --> 00:29:27,940
And who's this? Introduce her.

619
00:29:28,900 --> 00:29:29,740
My girlfriend.

620
00:29:30,050 --> 00:29:32,050
You lucky guy! Such a pretty girlfriend!

621
00:29:32,050 --> 00:29:34,530
Tell you what, I'll have the kitchen
make you two signature dishes.

622
00:29:34,530 --> 00:29:35,380
Go on, don't stand there.

623
00:29:35,380 --> 00:29:36,620
Alright, thanks. Let's go.

624
00:29:36,620 --> 00:29:38,420
- Go on up. Enjoy!
- Thanks.

625
00:29:38,570 --> 00:29:39,490
Hey,

626
00:29:39,490 --> 00:29:40,730
listen to me.

627
00:29:41,810 --> 00:29:43,980
Your judgment's flawed.

628
00:29:44,250 --> 00:29:45,330
Sitting here

629
00:29:45,330 --> 00:29:46,660
is more ergonomic

630
00:29:47,460 --> 00:29:49,460
than there.

631
00:29:51,900 --> 00:29:52,740
The left side.

632
00:29:53,290 --> 00:29:54,130
Right here.

633
00:29:55,770 --> 00:29:57,250
But I should warn you in advance.

634
00:29:57,570 --> 00:29:58,770
These people are all a bit quirky.

635
00:29:58,770 --> 00:30:00,050
So you'd better be mentally prepared.

636
00:30:01,010 --> 00:30:01,850
Okay.

637
00:30:02,730 --> 00:30:04,250
Then, welcome to

638
00:30:04,420 --> 00:30:05,330
the Oddball Club.

639
00:30:05,940 --> 00:30:06,980
You still need to learn...

640
00:30:08,900 --> 00:30:10,050
Hey, get back here!

641
00:30:13,420 --> 00:30:15,730
Last time, I told you
to keep an eye on that girl in the park.

642
00:30:15,730 --> 00:30:16,570
Where'd she go?

643
00:30:16,730 --> 00:30:18,570
Who did that? She left on her own.

644
00:30:18,730 --> 00:30:20,090
I came all this way

645
00:30:20,090 --> 00:30:21,620
just to wander alone?

646
00:30:21,620 --> 00:30:23,010
She was smart to leave

647
00:30:23,330 --> 00:30:24,380
when she knew you were coming.

648
00:30:25,050 --> 00:30:25,890
Cut the chatter.

649
00:30:26,180 --> 00:30:27,020
Down this drink

650
00:30:27,330 --> 00:30:28,330
as your apology.

651
00:30:28,660 --> 00:30:29,810
Let us have some fun.

652
00:30:29,980 --> 00:30:30,980
Hold on.

653
00:30:30,980 --> 00:30:31,980
Down it!

654
00:30:31,980 --> 00:30:33,180
I'm driving. No alcohol for me.

655
00:30:33,400 --> 00:30:34,250
Come on.

656
00:30:34,250 --> 00:30:35,090
Besides,

657
00:30:35,380 --> 00:30:37,620
whether I can drink depends
on your sister-in-law now.

658
00:30:38,860 --> 00:30:40,380
Sister-in-law?

659
00:30:40,980 --> 00:30:42,050
Come on, Xiaoxi.

660
00:30:42,900 --> 00:30:43,740
Here.

661
00:30:47,980 --> 00:30:48,820
Hello, everyone.

662
00:30:49,050 --> 00:30:50,140
I'm Jiang Yifan.

663
00:30:53,460 --> 00:30:54,300
Sister-in-law,

664
00:30:55,050 --> 00:30:56,530
have we met somewhere before?

665
00:30:56,530 --> 00:30:57,370
Yeah.

666
00:30:57,380 --> 00:30:58,250
Well...

667
00:30:58,250 --> 00:30:59,900
We met at Bei's shop.

668
00:30:59,900 --> 00:31:00,860
Right, right.

669
00:31:00,860 --> 00:31:01,700
That day...

670
00:31:01,810 --> 00:31:03,730
Welcome, gorgeous. Big welcome.

671
00:31:03,730 --> 00:31:04,570
Hello.

672
00:31:04,570 --> 00:31:05,420
Hey there.

673
00:31:06,380 --> 00:31:07,490
Do you have a girlfriend?

674
00:31:08,180 --> 00:31:09,020
What are you staring at?

675
00:31:09,020 --> 00:31:09,920
Never seen a beauty?

676
00:31:10,700 --> 00:31:12,620
This is the one I told you about,

677
00:31:12,940 --> 00:31:13,780
Gong.

678
00:31:14,730 --> 00:31:16,330
Hi, I'm...

679
00:31:17,420 --> 00:31:18,570
I'm Deep in the Alley.

680
00:31:23,050 --> 00:31:23,890
I like you.

681
00:31:24,010 --> 00:31:24,860
I like you...

682
00:31:25,900 --> 00:31:26,980
I've fallen for you.

683
00:31:32,330 --> 00:31:33,250
You're...

684
00:31:35,460 --> 00:31:36,300
Jiang...

685
00:31:47,700 --> 00:31:48,810
You're Jiang Rongrong, right?

686
00:31:49,290 --> 00:31:51,090
Are you out of your mind?

687
00:31:51,090 --> 00:31:52,380
We always hear

688
00:31:52,380 --> 00:31:53,660
Bei mention you.

689
00:31:54,090 --> 00:31:56,290
He keeps going on about
how amazing his girlfriend Rongrong is.

690
00:31:56,290 --> 00:31:57,730
Like she's practically perfect, right?

691
00:31:57,860 --> 00:31:59,900
Now that I've met you,
I see he wasn't exaggerating.

692
00:32:01,770 --> 00:32:02,730
Who's Jiang Rongrong?

693
00:32:03,330 --> 00:32:05,090
Ignore him, he's just being silly.

694
00:32:05,090 --> 00:32:05,940
No.

695
00:32:05,940 --> 00:32:06,810
Wrong person?

696
00:32:07,250 --> 00:32:08,140
My bad.

697
00:32:08,570 --> 00:32:09,420
Lucy.

698
00:32:09,900 --> 00:32:10,980
Got it right this time, huh?

699
00:32:10,980 --> 00:32:12,050
Can you stop already?

700
00:32:12,460 --> 00:32:13,330
Enough already?

701
00:32:13,330 --> 00:32:15,250
What's with that face?

702
00:32:15,250 --> 00:32:17,090
It surely can't be Jessica,
sister-in-law.

703
00:32:17,460 --> 00:32:18,900
This really isn't on me.

704
00:32:19,050 --> 00:32:19,980
He brings a girl

705
00:32:19,980 --> 00:32:21,490
without warning us.

706
00:32:22,290 --> 00:32:23,380
My apologies.

707
00:32:25,140 --> 00:32:26,180
Don't mind him.

708
00:32:26,180 --> 00:32:27,020
I'm telling you,

709
00:32:27,660 --> 00:32:28,980
he looks just like Ouyang Feng.

710
00:32:28,980 --> 00:32:30,490
You can befriend these others,

711
00:32:30,490 --> 00:32:31,620
but keep your distance from him.

712
00:32:32,770 --> 00:32:33,900
Never thought Bei

713
00:32:33,900 --> 00:32:35,660
had so many nicknames for me in private.

714
00:32:36,330 --> 00:32:37,730
But no matter what he calls me,

715
00:32:37,730 --> 00:32:38,860
I'm still his only girlfriend.

716
00:32:41,620 --> 00:32:42,460
That's no fun.

717
00:32:43,010 --> 00:32:44,330
Nice meeting everyone.

718
00:32:44,730 --> 00:32:46,220
Hope I can join you guys in the future.

719
00:32:46,220 --> 00:32:47,770
- Not drinking today.
- Let's gather more often.

720
00:32:47,770 --> 00:32:50,050
- Come on.
- Chat ideals, get wasted!

721
00:32:50,050 --> 00:32:50,890
- Sure.
- Welcome, welcome.

722
00:32:50,890 --> 00:32:51,770
Alright, I...

723
00:32:51,770 --> 00:32:53,770
But rest assured.
I won't steal him away, except...

724
00:32:53,940 --> 00:32:54,780
In bed.

725
00:32:55,700 --> 00:32:57,810
Hey, tone it down. That sounds awful.

726
00:33:00,980 --> 00:33:02,140
Does this mean

727
00:33:03,050 --> 00:33:04,570
you can't hang

728
00:33:04,570 --> 00:33:05,490
with us anymore?

729
00:33:07,570 --> 00:33:09,090
Why does my heart ache

730
00:33:09,330 --> 00:33:10,170
so badly

731
00:33:10,660 --> 00:33:11,810
like I'm dying?

732
00:33:11,810 --> 00:33:14,050
Go die then.

733
00:33:14,050 --> 00:33:15,570
Ignore them, that's just how they are.

734
00:33:15,570 --> 00:33:16,460
Come on, let's eat.

735
00:33:18,180 --> 00:33:19,020
Sis-in-law,

736
00:33:19,660 --> 00:33:21,010
do you have a twin

737
00:33:21,250 --> 00:33:22,140
as beautiful

738
00:33:22,140 --> 00:33:24,380
and sensible as you?

739
00:33:24,770 --> 00:33:26,090
I'm not asking for myself.

740
00:33:26,250 --> 00:33:27,530
I'm asking for Gong.

741
00:33:28,140 --> 00:33:28,980
Yeah.

742
00:33:29,570 --> 00:33:30,490
Isn't there

743
00:33:31,050 --> 00:33:32,900
someone who looks

744
00:33:33,090 --> 00:33:33,930
just like you?

745
00:33:34,900 --> 00:33:36,180
Like you were both made

746
00:33:36,180 --> 00:33:37,460
from the same mold?

747
00:33:43,660 --> 00:33:44,570
Sorry to disappoint you.

748
00:33:45,090 --> 00:33:45,940
I'm an only child.

749
00:33:50,860 --> 00:33:51,980
Here, let me introduce you.

750
00:33:53,860 --> 00:33:55,860
This dual-toned hair guy

751
00:33:56,180 --> 00:33:57,020
is Xiu.

752
00:33:57,220 --> 00:33:58,140
He runs a musical instrument shop

753
00:33:58,380 --> 00:34:00,530
and sometimes writes songs
that never sell.

754
00:34:02,010 --> 00:34:03,330
Your hairstyle's really cool.

755
00:34:03,620 --> 00:34:04,770
Keep it low-key, please.

756
00:34:05,090 --> 00:34:07,460
I've always admired
people with artistic talent.

757
00:34:07,810 --> 00:34:09,650
I'd love to hear your work sometime.

758
00:34:10,010 --> 00:34:11,610
A true wordsmith artist.

759
00:34:11,860 --> 00:34:12,820
Bei, take notes.

760
00:34:12,820 --> 00:34:13,980
Can you talk like a normal person?

761
00:34:13,980 --> 00:34:14,900
Sure.

762
00:34:14,900 --> 00:34:15,940
Aren't I learning every day?

763
00:34:19,940 --> 00:34:21,860
And this beauty is Luanluan.

764
00:34:21,860 --> 00:34:22,980
She's a stage actress.

765
00:34:23,380 --> 00:34:24,690
We treat her like a bro.

766
00:34:25,170 --> 00:34:26,010
I'm Luanluan.

767
00:34:26,210 --> 00:34:27,300
- Hi.
- Congrats to you.

768
00:34:27,300 --> 00:34:28,530
You found the best one

769
00:34:28,530 --> 00:34:29,370
among these men.

770
00:34:29,530 --> 00:34:30,740
Hey, I'm still right here.

771
00:34:31,650 --> 00:34:33,050
You're awesome, too.

772
00:34:33,900 --> 00:34:35,340
And this guy here.
Don't be fooled by him.

773
00:34:35,340 --> 00:34:36,180
His name's Gong.

774
00:34:36,690 --> 00:34:37,740
He might not look it,

775
00:34:37,900 --> 00:34:39,130
but he's actually a comic artist.

776
00:34:39,820 --> 00:34:41,530
My boyfriend...

777
00:34:42,170 --> 00:34:43,460
is a comic artist.

778
00:34:43,900 --> 00:34:45,570
Though he hasn't published
any comics yet,

779
00:34:45,570 --> 00:34:47,340
in my heart, he's still

780
00:34:48,130 --> 00:34:49,050
a true flirt master.

781
00:34:50,570 --> 00:34:52,090
Wait, what's a flirt master?

782
00:34:52,200 --> 00:34:53,050
Isn't that right?

783
00:34:53,050 --> 00:34:54,980
Did you drink too much to even draw now?

784
00:34:56,300 --> 00:34:57,780
I'd really love to see you draw.

785
00:34:58,860 --> 00:34:59,700
My bad.

786
00:34:59,900 --> 00:35:02,130
Wrong choice of words.
I should've said "indiscriminate".

787
00:35:02,340 --> 00:35:03,780
Guess you don't really get me then.

788
00:35:04,010 --> 00:35:04,980
I don't plan to.

789
00:35:04,980 --> 00:35:06,490
I've got three rules.

790
00:35:06,650 --> 00:35:08,780
First, I don't date clueless fools.

791
00:35:08,780 --> 00:35:10,420
Second, I stay away from gold diggers.

792
00:35:10,650 --> 00:35:11,650
And third,

793
00:35:14,900 --> 00:35:16,090
never go for someone already taken.

794
00:35:17,130 --> 00:35:19,380
Don't take it so seriously.
I might actually believe you.

795
00:35:21,050 --> 00:35:23,130
This guy is Sen.

796
00:35:24,130 --> 00:35:25,260
As in the "sen" that means forest?

797
00:35:25,260 --> 00:35:26,860
Yeah, the one with three trees.

798
00:35:27,210 --> 00:35:28,420
It stands for steadfast.

799
00:35:29,690 --> 00:35:30,780
What part of you is steadfast?

800
00:35:31,300 --> 00:35:32,140
Your hair?

801
00:35:32,380 --> 00:35:33,610
These are all my best friends.

802
00:35:33,610 --> 00:35:35,180
- Now you know everyone.
- Bei, is that all?

803
00:35:35,860 --> 00:35:37,490
Everyone else gets a bio.

804
00:35:37,490 --> 00:35:38,340
Why don't I get one?

805
00:35:38,340 --> 00:35:39,690
How's he supposed to describe you?

806
00:35:40,210 --> 00:35:41,340
Love repellent?

807
00:35:41,900 --> 00:35:42,840
Hopeless romantic?

808
00:35:43,350 --> 00:35:46,170
What's wrong with quietly
being a low-key bachelor?

809
00:35:46,170 --> 00:35:47,490
Who are you calling a bachelor?

810
00:35:48,690 --> 00:35:49,980
I've got a girlfriend, alright?

811
00:35:50,170 --> 00:35:52,170
And she's really gorgeous.

812
00:35:52,190 --> 00:35:53,030
I'd like some seeds.

813
00:35:53,030 --> 00:35:54,190
Let me be straight with you.

814
00:35:54,610 --> 00:35:56,980
We're getting along
pretty well right now.

815
00:35:56,980 --> 00:35:58,260
Things are developing nicely.

816
00:35:58,650 --> 00:36:00,570
Just no chance
to hang out with you guys now.

817
00:36:27,900 --> 00:36:28,940
(Yu)

818
00:36:30,650 --> 00:36:31,490
Hello?

819
00:36:33,170 --> 00:36:34,460
I'm writing songs at the shop.
What's up?

820
00:36:36,210 --> 00:36:37,460
How long have you two known each other?

821
00:36:38,610 --> 00:36:40,260
Counting today, it's been...

822
00:36:41,010 --> 00:36:41,900
96 days.

823
00:36:42,690 --> 00:36:43,780
If we get more specific,

824
00:36:43,780 --> 00:36:45,340
it's exactly 3 hours
and 31 minutes.

825
00:36:45,650 --> 00:36:46,530
I use this trick all the time.

826
00:36:46,530 --> 00:36:47,420
I can get it down to the exact second.

827
00:36:47,650 --> 00:36:49,130
Nobody thinks you're mute
if you shut up.

828
00:36:49,860 --> 00:36:51,460
Eat more, just focus on your plate.

829
00:36:52,010 --> 00:36:52,850
And you?

830
00:36:53,570 --> 00:36:55,260
How long have you been with Xiu?

831
00:36:58,010 --> 00:36:59,210
Sister-in-law, you've got a sharp eye.

832
00:36:59,780 --> 00:37:00,820
You noticed?

833
00:37:02,460 --> 00:37:03,340
You've got it wrong.

834
00:37:03,740 --> 00:37:05,650
Xiu and I are just close friends.

835
00:37:10,570 --> 00:37:12,010
How could this possibly hold me back?

836
00:37:12,340 --> 00:37:14,010
I already make a living writing songs.

837
00:37:14,170 --> 00:37:15,610
Why do you always insist that I...?

838
00:37:20,090 --> 00:37:21,740
Alright, let's drop it.

839
00:37:21,740 --> 00:37:22,590
Got a burst of inspiration.

840
00:37:22,590 --> 00:37:23,570
I'll head back later tonight.

841
00:37:23,980 --> 00:37:24,820
Bye.

842
00:37:34,321 --> 00:37:36,920
♪I admit it♪

843
00:37:36,921 --> 00:37:40,960
♪My back is against the wall♪

844
00:37:41,841 --> 00:37:45,360
♪There's nothing I wouldn't try to do♪

845
00:37:45,361 --> 00:37:49,920
♪For this feeling to have you♪

846
00:37:50,201 --> 00:37:52,400
♪I resist♪

847
00:37:52,721 --> 00:37:54,301
♪Your gaze, your lips♪

848
00:37:54,321 --> 00:37:56,920
♪Your touch is a gift♪

